#### Climate

According to the rather intricate [Köppen climate classification](/K%C3%B6ppen_climate_classification) system, Freehold Township occupies a precarious position on the northern boundary between the [humid subtropical climate](/Humid_subtropical_climate) (Cfa) zone and the [humid continental climate](/Humid_continental_climate) (Dfa) zone. This makes the township one of the most northerly localities in all of North America to exhibit a humid subtropical climate, a detail that might surprise those who associate such conditions with more southerly latitudes. Cfa climates, for those who appreciate the specifics, are characterized by all months maintaining an average temperature above 32.0 °F (0.0 °C), with at least four months registering an average temperature at or above 50.0 °F (10.0 °C). Furthermore, at least one month must achieve an average temperature at or above 71.6 °F (22.0 °C), all without any significant seasonal disparities in precipitation. It's a precise balance, much like everything else in the universe.

